    question: "What is the dryness of the separated sludge discharge of the decanter centrifuge?",
    answer: "The separated sludge discharge from a decanter centrifuge is typically about 50% dry. It commonly has a consistency of fudge or toothpaste. It is drip-free from well-adjusted decanters."
